===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|πολύεδρον}}, from {{m|grc|πολύς||many}} + {{m|grc|ἕδρα||seat}}; compare French {{m|fr|polyèdre}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{enPR|pŏlēhē'drən}}, {{IPA|/pɒliˈhiːdrən/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|polyhedra|polyhedrons}}

# {{label|en|geometry}} A [[solid]] [[figure]] with many flat [[face]]s and straight edges.
# {{label|en|optics}} A [[polyscope]], or multiplying glass.

